text: Paul Tratt was an American football player and coach. He served as the head football coach at Grinnell College in Grinnell, Iowa in 1901 and the University of Wisconsin–Whitewater in 1904. He was a college football player and four-year letter winner at the University of Wisconsin. ==References== Category:Year of birth missing Category:Year of death missing Category:American football quarterbacks Category:Grinnell Pioneers football coaches Category:Wisconsin Badgers football players Category:Wisconsin–Whitewater Warhawks football coaches
